  "text": "In line with the findings of [CITATION_1] , melanoma development was also suppressed in the majority of mice, irrespective of depletion of T CIRC cells, but protection was most pronounced in mice harboring both T CIRC and T RM cells. These studies clearly affirm the potential of intradermal vaccine-induced T RM cells to achieve potent protection against skin cancer. To effectively protect against malignancies, cancer vaccines should therefore evoke potent T RM cell responses within the tissue.",
